## Slides 2–29 — Chalk Character + Scribble Accents

**Status:** style locked 2026-06-09 (pilot 3) · style: hand-drawn chalk-character with white-chalk scribble accents (arrows / swirls / stars) + soft pastel chalk washes in warm muted tones · transparent PNG · aspect 1:1 square · placement varies per slide layout (see each entry).

**Shared style baked into each prompt:** "Hand-drawn chalkboard-style children's illustration combining chalk linework with soft pastel chalk washes. Drawn in loose textured white chalk and crayon strokes (visibly grainy, slightly imperfect edges) and filled with gentle pastel chalk smudges in muted warm tones — soft terracotta, mustard yellow, dusty teal, pale cream. Subject: [PER-SLIDE]. Surrounding the subject, scattered abstract white-chalk scribble accents (small swirly arrows, tiny stars, dotted motion-trails, looping squiggles — pure white chalk, sketchy and playful). PURE TRANSPARENT PNG BACKGROUND — no chalkboard surface, no scenery, no ground line, no shadow disc — just the chalky vignette and white-chalk scribbles floating alone on transparent so they sit naturally on a dark slide. No text, no logos, no realistic photographic faces, no flat vector shapes, no clean digital outlines. Square 1:1."

**Layout-awareness:** each subject below is composed to suit its placement — corner placements use a compact subject + a few scribbles; side placements (section slides) lean vertical; bottom-strip placements (slides 11, 22) lean horizontal/spread-out.

**Generation:** keep `GEMINI_IMAGE_ASPECT_RATIO=1:1`. One run processes the 25 pending markers — slides 2/11/17 are already archived from pilot 3 so they're skipped. After the script writes ImgBB URLs here, copy each URL into the matching `PENDING_SLIDE_N` placeholder in `credentials-access-platform-slides.md`.

